Package: libigraph
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.3.2)
Description: A library for creating and manipulating graphs.
 igraph is a library for creating and manipulating graphs.
 It is intended to be as powerful (ie. fast) as possible to enable the
 analysis of large graphs.
 .
 It was started as an additional package to the GNU R system, but most
 of its functions can also be used as a separate library. Additional
 Python bindings are also available as a separate package.
 .
 Homepage: http://cneuro.rmki.kfki.hu/projects/igraph

